### Feature 3: Constellation Travel Buttons in Preview Panel

**Goal**: When a star is selected, show "Fly to [title]" buttons for each constellation-linked star, similar to the existing wormhole button.

**Design Decision on Data Source**: Modify the SQL RPC `get_viewport_constellations` to also return `a_title` and `b_title` (following the exact pattern of `find_wormhole_pairs`). Reason:
- The `posts` Map in Universe.jsx only contains viewport-loaded stars. A constellation may link to a star far outside the current viewport that has never been fetched.
- The SQL already JOINs `journals ja` and `journals jb` -- adding `ja.title` and `jb.title` is trivial and costs nothing extra.
- Looking up from the posts Map would fail silently for distant stars, producing a poor UX with missing titles.

**Step 1: Update SQL RPC** (`server/sql/constellations.sql`)

```sql
DROP FUNCTION IF EXISTS get_viewport_constellations(UUID[]);
CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION get_viewport_constellations(post_ids UUID[])
RETURNS TABLE (
    id UUID, star_id_a UUID, star_id_b UUID,
    user_id_a UUID, user_id_b UUID,
    label TEXT, status TEXT, created_at TIMESTAMPTZ,
    a_universe_x DOUBLE PRECISION, a_universe_y DOUBLE PRECISION,
    b_universe_x DOUBLE PRECISION, b_universe_y DOUBLE PRECISION,
    a_title TEXT, b_title TEXT
) AS $$
BEGIN
    RETURN QUERY
    SELECT c.id, c.star_id_a, c.star_id_b, c.user_id_a, c.user_id_b,
           c.label, c.status, c.created_at,
           ja.universe_x AS a_universe_x, ja.universe_y AS a_universe_y,
           jb.universe_x AS b_universe_x, jb.universe_y AS b_universe_y,
           ja.title AS a_title, jb.title AS b_title
    FROM constellations c
    JOIN journals ja ON ja.id = c.star_id_a
    JOIN journals jb ON jb.id = c.star_id_b
    WHERE c.status IN ('accepted', 'pending')
      AND (c.star_id_a = ANY(post_ids) OR c.star_id_b = ANY(post_ids));
END;
$$ LANGUAGE plpgsql STABLE;
```

**Step 2: Universe.jsx -- Compute constellation links for selected post**

Add a helper function and a memo that finds all constellation links for the selected post:

```javascript
// New function, similar to getWormholeForPost
const getConstellationLinksForPost = useCallback((postId) => {
    if (!postId || acceptedConstellations.length === 0) return [];
    const links = [];
    for (const c of acceptedConstellations) {
        if (c.star_id_a === postId) {
            links.push({
                constellation: c,
                targetStarId: c.star_id_b,
                targetTitle: c.b_title || 'Unnamed Star',
                label: c.label,
            });
        } else if (c.star_id_b === postId) {
            links.push({
                constellation: c,
                targetStarId: c.star_id_a,
                targetTitle: c.a_title || 'Unnamed Star',
                label: c.label,
            });
        }
    }
    return links;
}, [acceptedConstellations]);
```

**Step 3: Universe.jsx -- Add constellation travel handler**

```javascript
const handleConstellationTravel = useCallback((targetStarId, constellation) => {
    if (isFlying.current) return;

    // Try finalStarPositions first (live computed), fall back to constellation raw coords
    let targetPos = finalStarPositions.get(targetStarId);
    if (!targetPos) {
        // Fall back to the constellation's stored universe coordinates
        const isTargetA = constellation.star_id_a === targetStarId;
        const rawX = isTargetA ? constellation.a_universe_x : constellation.b_universe_x;
        const rawY = isTargetA ? constellation.a_universe_y : constellation.b_universe_y;
        if (rawX != null && rawY != null) {
            targetPos = { x: rawX, y: rawY };
        }
    }
    if (!targetPos) return;

    setSelectedPost(null);
    flyTo(targetPos.x, targetPos.y, zoom);
}, [finalStarPositions, flyTo, isFlying, zoom]);
```

